The paper deals with list decoding of error-correcting codes, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses concatenated codes, which are a topic in data structures (cs.DS) and coding theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper discusses the decoding of Reed-Solomon codes, which are commonly used in signal processing (cs.SI).
